Cloud Market
2019 $216B -> AWS 45% Others 20% Azure 18%
2020 $371B
2025 $823B

AWS
	Launched 2006
	Over 190 countries & 18 global regions
	Over 1,000,000 active users
	Over 175 products and services
    - Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)**: Provides scalable computing capacity in the cloud to run virtual servers.
    - Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service)**: Offers scalable object storage for data backup, archival, and analytics.
    - Amazon RDS (Relational Database Service)**: Makes it easy to set up, operate, and scale a relational database in the cloud.
    - Amazon Lambda**: Allows you to run code without provisioning or managing servers, ideal for serverless computing.

Azure
	Public 2010
	Over 169 services
	Over 300k customers
	57 regions & 31 geographies
    - Azure Virtual Machines**: Provides scalable virtual machines running Windows or Linux.
    - Azure Blob Storage**: Offers massively scalable object storage for unstructured data.
    - Azure SQL Database**: A fully managed relational database with built-in intelligence.
    - Azure Functions**: Enables serverless compute capabilities to run event-driven code.

GCP
	Launches 2010
	Over 90 services 
	Idk users
    - Google Compute Engine**: Provides scalable virtual machines in the cloud.
    - Google Cloud Storage**: Offers unified object storage for developers and enterprises.
    - Google Cloud SQL**: A fully managed relational database service for MySQL, PostgreSQL, and SQL Server.
    - Google Cloud Functions**: Allows you to deploy event-driven serverless code functions.

Other Cloud Providers (20% in 2019)
	Tencent & Alibana in China
	IBM and Oracle
	Digital Ocean
	Private cloud providers
